LexiHint Privacy Policy
Last Updated: January 2026
Introduction
LexiHint ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our browser extension.
Information We Collect
Account Information
Email address (for registration and login)
Name (optional, from Google sign-in)
Usage Data
Translated words and vocabulary history
Learning statistics and progress
Website URLs where words are encountered (for context reference only)
Technical Data
Browser language settings
Extension preferences and settings
How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:
Provide translation and vocabulary learning services
Sync your vocabulary and progress across devices
Improve our translation accuracy and user experience
Process subscription payments (via third-party payment processors)
Data Storage and Security
All data is transmitted via HTTPS encryption
Authentication tokens are securely stored locally
Your data is stored on secure cloud servers (Supabase)
We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties
What We Do NOT Collect
Browsing history
Passwords
Payment card details (handled by third-party processors)
Personal communications
Location data
Your Rights
You have the right to:
Access your personal data
Delete your account and all associated data
Export your vocabulary data
Opt out of data collection by uninstalling the extension
Third-Party Services
We use the following third-party services:
Supabase: For authentication and data storage
Google Sign-In: For optional account authentication
Payment Processors: For subscription payments
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Email: HTuring1024@protonmail.com
